    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-09-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-09-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Denby</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 21,
                                    1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1151.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to previous correspondence in
                            regard to the permission sought of the Russian Government for our
                            missionaries in China to take refuge in Russian territory should their
                            lives be endangered by Chinese mobs, I have to inform you that a
                            telegram, dated September 17, from our minister at St. Petersburg,
                            advises the Department that the desired permission has been granted
                            without the imposition of any previous conditions on those seeking
                            refuge.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
